To differentiate \(f(x)=\cot x\), write it as \(\displaystyle\frac{\cos x}{\sin x}\) and use the quotient rule:

\(f'(x)=\frac{(\!-\sin x)\,\sin x-\cos x\cos x}{\sin^2x}
=\frac{-\sin^2x-\cos^2x}{\sin^2x}
=-\frac{1}{\sin^2x}
=-\csc^2x.\)

Therefore,  
\[
\frac{d}{dx}\bigl(\cot x\bigr)=-\csc^2x.
\]
